Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

== Slaw ==

In a #small bowl{} combine the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and @mayonnaise{40%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir well to combine and set aside.

== Onion Crumb ==

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Put the @British hickory smoked sausages{2} on a lightly oiled baking tray. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

== Onion Crumb ==

Toss the diced onion in the @plain flour{60%g} in a #bowl{} and season with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, fry the onion until coloured and crispy, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir occasionally to prevent them from burning. Transfer to some #kitchen paper{} to absorb any excess oil.

== Assembly ==

Slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} through the middle (but not all the way through) and pop them in the oven for ~{2%minutes}. When hot place the buns on your #plates{} and spread half the @BBQ sauce{32%g} inside each, then fill with a sausage. Spoon over the remaining BBQ sauce and top with the grated cheese. Sprinkle over the crispy onions. Serve the wedges on the side along with the slaw. Enjoy!